extends layout
include games/blocks.pug

block content
  div.container
    div.box
        h1 Emanuel (Hazel) Charron-Blais
        p.bySide Game Developer / Designer
        p.bySide They/She
        p.bySide NB, Canada 
        a.bySide(href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/emanuel-charron-blais-8a42a0302/") Linkedin: https://www.linkedin.com/in/emanuel-charron-blais-8a42a0302/
        p.bySide 📧 Email: naradoxy@gmail.com
        a.bySide(href="portfolio") CV: https://naradoxy.github.io/hazelWebsite/portfolio
    img.face(src="images/myFace2.jpg", alt="Emanuel's profile image")
  div.container
    img(src="images/sbadge.png", alt="Game Designer UofT Badge")
    div.box
      h5 Circuit Stream Certified Professional Game Designer | University of Toronto School of Continuing Studies
      a(href="https://www.credly.com/organizations/circuit-stream/badges") Issued by Circuit Stream
  div.box
    h2 Summary / Objective
    p I'm a lifelong gamer turned developer who's built game projects since age 10.
    p Passionate about small-team collaboration and crafting memorable gameplay experiences.
    p Seeking a junior role where I can help bring creative visions to life while learning from seasoned devs.
  div.box
    h2 Highlights
    p Created a Minecraft mod with over 1000 downloads
    p Ranked Overall #19 out of 124 entries in a gamejam
    p Made many fully networked multiplayer games
    p Skilled with self teaching from a young age
    p Uploaded games to itch.io since 2020
  div.box
    h2 Skills
    p Engines: Godot (primary), Unreal, Gamemaker
    p Languages: C#, GDScript, GDShader, GameMakerLanguage, Java, JavaScript, HTML/CSS, Pug
    p Tools & Art: Krita, DaVinci Resolve, Blender (basic), Paint.NET, Audacity, Soundtrap, FL Studio
    p Version Control: Git, Github, Sourcetree, Github Desktop
  div.box
    h2 About me
    p I enjoy drawing, sometimes making music, playing games to get all the achievements, taking care of my cats, and certainly making games.
    p All this time I've been making games pretty much solo, but I am so excited to take the next steps and delve into the industry and work in a team who love games as genuinely as I do.
    p For me, it's not just about finishing a game; It's about the process and crafting an experience for others to enjoy.
  div.box
    h2 Education
    p Game Design Course, CircuitStream (via University of Toronto)
    p Teaches students deep knowledge on game design and prepares them for the industry.
    p   Feb 2025 - Sep 2025
    p High School Diploma, École Polyvalente Louis-J.-Robichaud
    p   Graduated 2024
  div.box
    h2 Additional
    p Languages: English (fluent), Français (first language), Dutch (learning)
    p Art & Audio: Personal art (Krita), quick‑prototype art (Paint.NET), music (Soundtrap and FL Studio)
  div.box
    h2 Highlight Projects:
  +game("hbt")
  +game("dm")
  +game("dd")
  +game("pb")
